 be considered when methotrexate is used with other potentially hepatotoxic agents (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/106211/', '', 'Ustekinumab, Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Anifrolumab, Canakinumab, Secukinumab, Ravulizumab, Diroximel fumarate, Abatacept, Upadacitinib, Siponimod, Anakinra, More', 'Tinidazole, Oritavancin, Daptomycin, Methenamine, Spectinomycin, Fosfomycin, Lefamulin, Dalbavancin', 1767369485);
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO drug_interactions (id, ingredient1, ingredient2, severity, effect, source, management_text, mechanism_text, recommendation, risk_level, type, metabolism_info, source_url, reference_text, alternatives_a, alternatives_b, updated_at) VALUES (106089, 'Nitrous oxide', 'Methotrexate', 'Major', 'The use of nitrous oxide anesthesia may increase the risk of methotrexate-associated cytotoxicity. The proposed mechanism is that nitrous oxide increases the effects of methotrexate on tetrahydrofolate metabolism, resulting in greater toxicity.', 'DDInter', 'The concomitant use of nitrous oxide anesthesia with methotrexate should be avoided. Some authorities consider the use of nitrous oxide with methotrexate to be contraindicated (CA). If concomitant use is unavoidable, patients should be closely monitored for toxicity during the postoperative period. Intravenous hydration and calcium folinate (leucovorin) are recommended to decrease the incidence of methotrexate toxicity.', 'Synergism', 'The concomitant use of nitrous oxide anesthesia with methotrexate should be avoided.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/106212/', '', 'Golimumab, Cyclosporine, Ustekinumab, Antithymocyte immunoglobulin (rabbit), Tocilizumab, Secukinumab, Canakinumab, Anifrolumab, Ravulizumab, Diroximel fumarate, Mycophenolic acid, More', 'Halothane, Thiopental, Alfentanil, Remifentanil, Sodium oxybate, Methohexital, Desflurane, Sufentanil, Enflurane, Esketamine, Sevoflurane, More', 1767369485);
